The paper deals with the problem of polynomial factoring over finite fields, which is a well-studied topic in computational complexity and cryptography. The paper also introduces a new algebraic-combinatorial framework called m-schemes, which has applications in coding theory and graph theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SD (Systems and Control), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
